public abstract class

NavigationProviderService

extends Service
java.lang.Object
   ↳ android.content.Context
     ↳ android.content.ContextWrapper
       ↳ android.app.Service
         ↳ com.google.android.apps.auto.sdk.nav.NavigationProviderService

Class Overview

A base service implementation for a navigation provider service.

Example Implementation: 

public class MyNavService extends NavigationProviderService {
     private NavigationStateManager mStateManager;
     private NavigationSuggestionManager mSuggestionManager;

     {@literal @}Override
     protected int getMaxSupportedVersion() {
         return MAX_VERSION;
     }
     {@literal @}Override
     protected int getMinSupportedVersion() {
         return MIN_VERSION;
     }
     {@literal @}Override
     protected void onAndroidAutoStart(ClientMode clientMode) {
         super.onAndroidAutoStart(clientMode);
         mSuggestionManager.sendNavigationSuggestions(...);
         mStateManager.sendNavigationSummary(...);
         mStateManager.sendTurnEvent(...);
     }
     {@literal @}Override
     protected NavigationStateManager getNavigationStateManager() {
         return mStateManager;
     }
     {@literal @}Override
     protected NavigationSuggestionManager getNavigationSuggestionManager() {
         return mSuggestionManager;
     }
 }

The implementing service should also be declared in the manifest. 

<service android:name="com.example.MyNavService" android:exported="true">
     <intent-filter>
         <action android:name="android.intent.action.MAIN" />
         <category android:name="com.google.android.car.category.NAVIGATION_PROVIDER" />
     </intent-filter>
 </service>

Implementing services should use the instances of managers returned by getNavigationStateManager() or getNavigationSuggestionManager() to communicate with the navigation client.

Note: Binding to this service is not protected by a permission. Any call on the returned Binder will throw a SecurityException if the calling UID does not correspond to an Android Auto signed package. Any subclass that overrides onBind(Intent) to return multiple Binder implementations is responsible for securing data in Binders not returned by the superclass.
